text: As a child, you would wait, and watch from far away.
But you always knew that you'd be the one
That'd work while they all play
In youth, you'd lay, awake at night and scheme
Of all the things that you would change
But it was just a dream.
Here we are, don't turn away now.
We are the Warriors that built this town!
Here we are, don't turn away now.
We are the Warriors that built this town! From dust.
The time will come, when you will have to rise.
Above the rest, improve yourself, your spirit never dies.
Farewell, I've gone, to take my throne above.
But don't weep for me, cause this will be
The labour of my love.
